summary: An ordinance appropriating the sum of $100 out of the general fund of the City of Seattle, to pay the claim of Marie J. Howard, et vir., for personal injuries received by Marie J. Howard on the 19th day of May, 1916, while walking on the sidewalk located in front of No. 128 Westlake Avenue, in the City of Seattle, and authorizing the drawing of a warrant therefor.
